WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:27.160 --> 00:29.288
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

00:31.373 --> 00:33.842
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

00:51.935 --> 00:56.361
There's a trading post 35 miles
northeast of here in the great plateau.

00:58.275 --> 01:01.279
Ten miles north of that
is a landing strip.

01:01.528 --> 01:05.783
We can have the film pouched out to
Delphi, then send it on to Calcutta.

01:06.783 --> 01:10.037
Old Jonesy should be happy.
We're only two weeks late.

01:12.289 --> 01:15.293
This has been such a wonderful adventure.

01:15.667 --> 01:17.214
You made it wonderful.

01:26.637 --> 01:28.197
Mark it down in your book.

01:28.347 --> 01:31.317
September, the Amazon. July, Egypt. Okay?

01:32.142 --> 01:34.190
But in the next five minutes, bed.

01:34.770 --> 01:37.114
[WILDLIFE CHATTERING]

01:42.694 --> 01:45.163
[SPEAKING IN NATIVE LANGUAGE]

02:05.926 --> 02:08.223
[HORSE WHINNYING]

02:23.694 --> 02:25.947
[HORSE PANICKING]

02:36.790 --> 02:38.463
[RESTRAINTS BREAK]

02:40.836 --> 02:42.133
[SHOUTING IN NATIVE LANGUAGE]

02:55.308 --> 02:57.436
[GROWLING]

03:07.028 --> 03:09.372
- [ANIMAL SNARLING]
- [SCREAMING]

03:35.140 --> 03:36.107
No!

03:37.350 --> 03:39.369
[SCREAMING]

03:39.519 --> 03:40.566
No!

03:43.815 --> 03:45.408
[SCREAMING]

04:13.345 --> 04:15.030
- [GUN COCKS]
- [ROARING]

04:15.180 --> 04:17.023
[GUNSHOT]

06:00.243 --> 06:02.712
Ready, boy? Come on. Come get it!

06:03.705 --> 06:05.673
Come on. You want the ball, Thor?

06:06.124 --> 06:09.003
You want the ball? Yeah, come on.

06:09.169 --> 06:10.479
Hey, you ready, Thor?

06:10.629 --> 06:12.677
Come on, go get it! Go get it!

06:14.633 --> 06:15.942
Bring it back, Thor.

06:16.092 --> 06:17.594
Come on, Thor, come here!

06:18.762 --> 06:20.856
Hey Thor, come here, give me the ball.

06:22.140 --> 06:23.517
Hey Thor, come here!

06:24.434 --> 06:26.357
Come back here, Thor!
Come on, give me the ball.

06:26.853 --> 06:28.196
Thor, come here!

06:28.855 --> 06:30.698
I'm going to get you, boy!

06:33.985 --> 06:35.703
Where you going, boy?

06:41.159 --> 06:42.627
Where's the ball?

07:03.682 --> 07:05.200
Nice doggy.

07:05.350 --> 07:07.193
- [CLICKS TONGUE]
- [BARKS]

07:10.188 --> 07:11.610
Nice doggy.

07:12.565 --> 07:14.909
You're a big one, aren't ya?
Are you a dog or a horse?

07:15.110 --> 07:17.879
It's not a horse. It's a German Shepherd.

07:18.029 --> 07:19.381
Yeah?

07:19.531 --> 07:22.080
Well, he's a hell of a big
German Shepherd, ain't he?

07:23.201 --> 07:24.248
May I help you?

07:25.996 --> 07:28.590
- You must be the lady of the house?
- Yes, I am.

07:28.832 --> 07:30.425
I see you got a young boy here.

07:30.750 --> 07:33.219
Now, you help him
get the best education possible?

07:33.378 --> 07:36.222
Because I represent the Pacific
Northwest Magna Reading Project

07:36.464 --> 07:38.567
and we have a series of books
which studies have proved

07:38.717 --> 07:40.402
are a major benefit towards
advanced learning in

07:40.552 --> 07:42.179
phonetics and word comprehension.

07:42.345 --> 07:45.532
Now, if I could have just five minutes
of your valuable time to show you

07:45.682 --> 07:46.899
this exquisite series, I'm sure
you won't be disappointed.

07:48.018 --> 07:49.452
Thank you very much,
but we're really not interested

07:49.602 --> 07:52.276
- in buying anything right now.
- No, please. Please.

07:52.772 --> 07:55.525
Let me show you these books
my company has developed, all right?

07:55.900 --> 07:57.252
I have them right...

07:57.402 --> 07:59.212
[GROWLING]

07:59.362 --> 08:01.298
- ...here.
- [BARKING]

08:01.448 --> 08:03.300
- Whoa, whoa, lady, whoa!
- Thor!

08:03.450 --> 08:05.418
Whoa, you ever heard of a leash law?

08:06.036 --> 08:08.763
Jeez, want to control that dog
before it bites somebody?

08:08.913 --> 08:10.756
- [BARKING]
- Thor!

08:14.836 --> 08:16.062
Hey, Thor!

08:16.212 --> 08:17.397
[SNARLING]

08:17.547 --> 08:19.970
- Hey, get off him, Thor!
- Get him off me!

08:20.467 --> 08:22.890
Hey, go to the house!
Go to the house, go on!

08:27.891 --> 08:30.064
- Are you okay?
- No, he bit me!

08:31.728 --> 08:33.788
- Jesus!
- Where did he bite you?

08:33.938 --> 08:36.066
You've got a dangerous animal there, lady.

08:39.986 --> 08:41.328
I'm suing.

08:41.738 --> 08:43.840
You better get hold of a lawyer
right away, lady,

08:43.990 --> 08:46.163
because you're gonna hear
from mine, toot sweet!

08:52.957 --> 08:54.425
You can talk to me.

08:56.252 --> 08:57.595
I'm a lawyer.

09:01.174 --> 09:02.517
[BARKING]

09:02.675 --> 09:04.361
Thor, sit and stay down!

09:04.511 --> 09:06.354
[WHIMPERING]

09:07.472 --> 09:08.724
Did he bite you?

09:09.974 --> 09:12.786
Because if he did, you really
need to see a doctor right away.

09:12.936 --> 09:16.731
Since you're on foot, I'll drive you
to the hospital emergency room myself.

09:17.982 --> 09:21.044
In fact, why don't I take you
to my own family doctor?

09:21.194 --> 09:23.162
No, no, no, I got my own doctor.

09:25.281 --> 09:26.373
All right.

09:27.033 --> 09:28.831
I've heard about enough, Flopsy.

09:29.035 --> 09:30.833
Who's Flopsy, mom?

09:31.204 --> 09:34.083
A flopsy, Brett, is a con man
who does things like

09:34.457 --> 09:37.051
throw himself in front of cars
and pretend to get hit

09:37.377 --> 09:41.473
or intentionally provoke people's
dogs and pretend to get bitten.

09:41.881 --> 09:45.135
He threatens to sue people
or have their pets destroyed

09:45.385 --> 09:47.137
if they don't pay him money.

09:48.513 --> 09:51.232
I've prosecuted plenty of these guys.

09:51.432 --> 09:55.328
- Yeah, well, then I'll see you in court.
- Brett, why don't you call Sheriff Bragg.

09:55.478 --> 09:57.664
Tell him you're my son.
He'll take the call.

09:57.814 --> 10:01.159
Tell him we got a little problem up here
and to send a deputy right away.

10:04.154 --> 10:06.873
Well, Flopsy, it's been
really nice knowing you.

10:07.031 --> 10:09.659
I guess I'll visit you in the slammer.

10:10.201 --> 10:11.219
Oh, you..

10:11.369 --> 10:12.512
[BARKING]

10:12.662 --> 10:13.879
Stay!

10:14.038 --> 10:18.005
My advice is to you is to turn around and
walk away without saying another word

10:18.209 --> 10:19.882
and without looking back.

10:20.336 --> 10:23.089
Yeah? Well, you ain't
heard the last of this, lady.

10:23.548 --> 10:25.141
Oh, I think I have.

10:25.967 --> 10:27.969
But don't think of it as a total loss.

10:28.469 --> 10:30.312
You learned a valuable lesson.

10:31.556 --> 10:34.856
Do not mess with a lawyer on her own turf.

11:43.127 --> 11:44.729
- Good night, Thor.
- [BLOWS KISS]

11:44.879 --> 11:46.347
[WHIMPERING]

12:30.258 --> 12:32.010
Lousy night shift.

12:34.554 --> 12:36.022
Overtime.

12:55.033 --> 12:56.831
[DISTANT GROWLING]

12:59.120 --> 13:00.246
Nah.

13:23.394 --> 13:25.647
[GROWLING GROWING CLOSER]

13:29.192 --> 13:31.127
23.7.

13:31.277 --> 13:33.120
[GROWLING]

14:10.400 --> 14:12.778
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

14:34.465 --> 14:36.888
- [ROARING]
- [SCREAMING]

14:38.845 --> 14:41.394
[HOWLING]

14:47.103 --> 14:49.356
[PHONE RINGING]

14:52.442 --> 14:53.659
Hello?

14:54.569 --> 14:55.786
Ted!

14:57.113 --> 14:58.631
Hi, how are you?

14:58.781 --> 15:00.078
Where are you?

15:02.326 --> 15:04.637
You've been back that long
and you haven't called me?

15:04.787 --> 15:06.289
You creep!

15:08.416 --> 15:10.839
Of course, we'd love to see you!

15:11.002 --> 15:13.630
Yeah, we'll be up to the lake
in a few hours.

15:33.649 --> 15:36.118
I thought Uncle Ted
was in another country.

15:36.360 --> 15:37.295
So did I.

15:37.445 --> 15:40.073
He's been back three months
and he didn't even call me.

15:40.990 --> 15:42.742
That flaky brother of mine!

16:08.976 --> 16:10.319
[THOR BARKING]

16:15.858 --> 16:17.451
[CHUCKLING]

16:23.324 --> 16:24.450
Hey!

16:25.993 --> 16:27.595
Hey, sis. How are you?

16:27.745 --> 16:29.463
How are you?

16:31.666 --> 16:33.885
Ever think of using that razor
I got you for Christmas?

16:34.043 --> 16:35.770
Yeah, maybe to slit my throat.

16:35.920 --> 16:38.106
God it's good to see you, Janet,
you don't know how good it is.

16:38.256 --> 16:40.066
Oh, that's right, that's why
you've been back two months

16:40.216 --> 16:42.639
and you don't call, you don't
tell me where you are, you don't...

16:43.219 --> 16:44.779
You putz!

16:44.929 --> 16:46.322
It's good to see you, too.

16:46.472 --> 16:48.520
Hey Brett, look at you,
you shot up like a weed.

16:48.933 --> 16:51.311
Uncle Ted, can I shoot the rifle?

16:51.686 --> 16:55.031
Well, maybe we'd better
talk about that later, okay?

16:55.356 --> 16:57.279
Come on, let's go in and visit.

17:40.943 --> 17:44.698
So sis, how's it going at the new firm,
Janeway and Samuels?

17:44.947 --> 17:47.216
So far, so good.
My caseload's a lot lighter

17:47.366 --> 17:49.619
than it was in the DA's office in Chicago.

17:49.827 --> 17:51.750
Pace is a lot easier.

17:52.163 --> 17:55.884
And, frankly, I am so glad
to be out of criminal litigation.

17:57.001 --> 17:59.470
How are you adjusting to small-town life?

18:00.004 --> 18:01.551
For me, like that!

18:01.922 --> 18:04.025
For Brett, it's not such
an easy adjustment, though.

18:04.175 --> 18:06.473
He hasn't made any friends
in the neighborhood.

18:06.636 --> 18:10.231
But Chicago's no place to raise kids.
Out here, it's safe and peaceful.

18:10.389 --> 18:12.437
You know, sis, I'm so proud of you.

18:12.642 --> 18:14.690
I really have to take my hat off to you.

18:15.019 --> 18:18.443
You're a full-time mom to Brett and still
manage to work at the firm full-time.

18:18.648 --> 18:19.900
It's just great.

18:26.405 --> 18:27.372
Hey.

18:29.492 --> 18:31.244
You're not telling me something.

18:33.663 --> 18:37.754
Things haven't been going so good for me
since I got back from the jungle, sis.

18:41.837 --> 18:43.430
Marjorie's gone.

18:43.673 --> 18:45.141
I'm sorry.

18:46.717 --> 18:48.936
Yeah, so now it's just me and...

18:50.680 --> 18:52.057
my shadow.

18:57.311 --> 18:59.484
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]

19:12.243 --> 19:13.620
Whoa!

19:17.707 --> 19:19.425
Oh, man.

19:36.684 --> 19:37.810
What?

19:55.953 --> 19:58.752
[MOUTHING THE TITLE]

20:07.131 --> 20:08.474
Whoa.

20:47.922 --> 20:50.471
- [BIRDS SQUAWKING]
- [THOR BARKING]

21:26.627 --> 21:27.799
[THOR BARKS]

21:28.879 --> 21:30.301
Thor!

21:32.049 --> 21:34.017
Don't do that to me!

21:36.512 --> 21:38.514
Good dog, Thor.

21:39.682 --> 21:41.184
Oh, shoot!

21:47.565 --> 21:49.943
- I haven't seen him.
- I wouldn't worry about him.

21:52.027 --> 21:53.199
Hey, sweetie.

21:53.946 --> 21:55.368
Hey, Thor.

21:58.993 --> 22:01.371
Come say hello to your Uncle Ted, Thor.

22:05.749 --> 22:08.102
That's our Thor. Overprotective.

22:08.252 --> 22:10.050
Maybe if he saw you more...

22:11.255 --> 22:12.222
Come.

22:12.423 --> 22:13.515
Come come.

22:14.008 --> 22:15.851
[WHIMPERING]

22:22.766 --> 22:25.986
We're two of a kind, aren't we, old pal?

22:28.105 --> 22:30.403
What did you do, spit in his Alpo?

22:30.900 --> 22:33.323
He knows an old dog when he sees one.

22:52.922 --> 22:56.016
Hey, you guys better get moving
if you want to get him home by bedtime.

22:56.258 --> 22:57.851
You have a long ride ahead of you, sis.

22:59.970 --> 23:01.989
I want you to stay with us for a while.

23:02.139 --> 23:04.267
I didn't realize how late it was,
come on, I'll walk you to the car.

23:04.475 --> 23:05.910
I mean it, I'm worried about you.

23:06.060 --> 23:07.277
Don't worry about me, come on.

23:07.478 --> 23:08.946
- Just say yes.
- Yes.

23:09.647 --> 23:11.165
Good. You're coming with us.

23:11.315 --> 23:12.666
No, but I'll come by soon.

23:12.816 --> 23:13.918
When?

23:14.068 --> 23:15.991
- I'll call you.
- This week.

23:16.320 --> 23:18.243
- This week.
- Good.

23:20.991 --> 23:22.208
Come on.

23:22.493 --> 23:24.166
- Come on, Thor!
- [BARKING]

23:59.655 --> 24:01.578
[PHONE RINGING]

24:06.662 --> 24:08.790
- Hello?
- Sis?

24:08.956 --> 24:10.333
Hey, Ted, how are you doing?

24:10.666 --> 24:12.168
Yeah, you know...

24:13.043 --> 24:15.104
having you up here was really great, sis.

24:15.254 --> 24:17.177
It really lifted my spirits a lot.

24:18.757 --> 24:20.179
Frankly, sis,

24:20.384 --> 24:21.351
you know,

24:21.593 --> 24:22.719
it's everything.

24:23.721 --> 24:24.847
It's everything.

24:25.222 --> 24:28.200
I just wanted to tell you
how much I appreciated

24:28.350 --> 24:30.273
your guy's trip up here and...

24:31.020 --> 24:32.272
family...

24:33.856 --> 24:35.233
It's all we've got, sis.

24:35.733 --> 24:37.585
Is there a problem up there?

24:37.735 --> 24:38.861
Problem?

24:40.029 --> 24:41.121
Up here?

24:45.075 --> 24:46.622
No, no problem at all.

24:53.042 --> 24:54.268
Just, uh,

24:54.418 --> 24:56.386
having you here, like I said...

24:57.880 --> 24:59.382
really lifted my spirits.

25:00.924 --> 25:02.471
I reckon maybe you're right.

25:02.843 --> 25:05.016
So I was thinking if
it's not an imposition...

25:07.556 --> 25:09.399
maybe I can visit you for a few days.

25:09.600 --> 25:12.479
Oh, Ted, you know
you're always welcome up here.

25:12.644 --> 25:14.146
Here's what you're gonna do:

25:14.438 --> 25:16.582
You're gonna park your
Airstream in the backyard

25:16.732 --> 25:18.575
and you're gonna live out of my fridge.

25:27.117 --> 25:28.414
Here's to family, sis.

25:28.619 --> 25:31.668
And having you next door to me,
just like when we were kids.

25:32.456 --> 25:35.005
It's perfect, just nice to be
out of the woods, all the memories.

25:35.292 --> 25:36.919
I'm always right, little brother.

25:38.087 --> 25:40.681
Yeah, it's really annoying.
Always has been.

25:41.673 --> 25:43.346
Honestly, I'm glad you're here.

25:43.926 --> 25:45.018
Me, too.

25:48.889 --> 25:50.866
Hey, Thor, come on, get out of there!

25:51.016 --> 25:53.064
Hey, hey, hey, Thor! Thor!

25:58.982 --> 26:00.334
Handcuffs? Ted!

26:00.484 --> 26:02.953
- Sis, it's not what you think.
- What are these?

26:03.445 --> 26:06.590
"Maximum Security High-Tempered Steel."

26:06.740 --> 26:08.663
- It's not what you think.
- Ooh, baby!

26:09.118 --> 26:11.541
I think I better keep my eye on you.

26:11.787 --> 26:14.210
It's gonna be real
interesting having you around.

26:14.998 --> 26:16.875
Come on. I'm gonna make dinner.

26:17.167 --> 26:19.545
No, thanks, I'm just gonna put on
my sweats and go for a run.

26:19.795 --> 26:23.675
I'm gonna keep a low profile tonight.
If that's all right with you?

26:24.007 --> 26:27.557
You can come and go as you please,
as long as you follow my rules.

26:28.512 --> 26:30.310
Come on, Thor! Come on!

26:59.042 --> 27:00.339
Good night, Thor.

27:32.534 --> 27:34.457
[THOR BARKING]

27:38.874 --> 27:40.126
What the hell?

27:48.884 --> 27:49.976
What's going on?

27:50.135 --> 27:52.529
Thor! What's wrong? What?

27:52.679 --> 27:53.851
What?

27:54.556 --> 27:57.730
Come on. You want to go outside?
Okay, go on, out, out!

27:59.770 --> 28:01.772
[CONTINUES BARKING]

28:13.784 --> 28:16.537
[DISTANT GROWLING]

28:38.100 --> 28:40.353
[ROARING]

28:46.441 --> 28:48.409
[THOR GROWLING]

28:54.366 --> 28:55.868
[WHIMPERING]

28:58.996 --> 29:01.431
[BARKING]

29:01.581 --> 29:04.334
Thor! Come here, boy!

29:05.711 --> 29:07.271
Thor, where are you?

29:07.421 --> 29:09.264
[BARKING]

29:12.801 --> 29:14.144
Thor!

29:19.558 --> 29:20.730
Thor!

29:21.852 --> 29:23.650
Thor, come on.

29:27.065 --> 29:28.237
Hey, hey.

29:28.859 --> 29:30.406
Good boy. Come on.

29:30.652 --> 29:32.495
Let's go! Come on!

29:33.488 --> 29:34.410
Come on!

29:34.656 --> 29:36.158
What's with you? Hey!

29:36.366 --> 29:38.334
What? What?

29:38.535 --> 29:40.663
Let's go home. Okay?

29:41.663 --> 29:43.916
You're such a baby.
Come on, come on, let's go.

29:44.166 --> 29:45.258
Come on!

29:45.542 --> 29:48.637
What? What's the deal with you?
Come on, we've got to go home.

29:49.379 --> 29:51.427
Jesus, ever heard of sleep?

29:52.341 --> 29:54.059
You crazy dog!

29:54.468 --> 29:55.594
Come on.

30:00.891 --> 30:03.519
You were at his funeral.

30:04.061 --> 30:07.031
You had quite a long relationship
with your boyfriend, Darnelle.

30:07.230 --> 30:09.082
We were together for three years.

30:09.232 --> 30:10.292
Three years.

30:10.442 --> 30:12.085
Thor!

30:12.235 --> 30:14.363
Come on! Let's go!

30:14.905 --> 30:16.782
Come on, you love baseball.

30:20.744 --> 30:22.371
Where are you going?

30:28.919 --> 30:30.842
Thor! Don't do that!

30:31.254 --> 30:32.972
Come here, Thor.

30:34.508 --> 30:36.977
Get over here, you knucklehead.

30:38.595 --> 30:40.893
That wasn't very nice.

30:42.974 --> 30:44.117
During the course of our show...

30:44.267 --> 30:47.737
We interrupt this program
to bring you a special news bulletin.

30:47.938 --> 30:52.459
Teams of hunters and police are patrolling
a 50-mile square area in Timberline

30:52.609 --> 30:54.907
as the curfew enters its third day.

30:55.278 --> 30:58.757
Police revealed today the shocking
discovery of a fifth dead hiker

30:58.907 --> 31:00.705
in the woods near Timberline.

31:01.118 --> 31:05.514
The five men and women were mutilated by
what authorities believe is a wild animal.

31:05.664 --> 31:07.541
Possibly a grizzly bear.

31:07.916 --> 31:11.561
Teams of hunters and bloodhounds
are patrolling a 50-mile square area

31:11.711 --> 31:14.555
and a curfew is now in effect
on Timberline.

31:14.965 --> 31:17.969
This is Sarah Williams reporting for KBDL.

31:30.897 --> 31:32.740
[THOR GROWLING]

31:48.665 --> 31:49.882
Hi, Thor.

31:51.460 --> 31:52.962
Come on, Thor.

31:53.170 --> 31:54.217
Let's go.

31:56.798 --> 31:57.970
Hey, Ted, good morning.

31:59.176 --> 32:00.428
Good morning, sis.

32:01.678 --> 32:04.948
Why didn't you tell me
about that curfew up in Timberline?

32:05.098 --> 32:06.645
Those hikers who were killed?

32:06.808 --> 32:09.311
That crazy animal that's loose up there?

32:09.686 --> 32:11.063
I just saw it on TV.

32:11.688 --> 32:13.540
There were police everywhere.

32:13.690 --> 32:15.533
Oh, uh...

32:15.692 --> 32:17.069
that, I uh,

32:17.360 --> 32:19.988
I was going to tell you about it
this morning, sis.

32:21.031 --> 32:24.911
Well, I guess this means you'll have to stay
until they lift the curfew, huh?

32:26.703 --> 32:28.000
I guess.

32:28.705 --> 32:30.332
So you want some breakfast?

32:30.665 --> 32:31.757
Yeah, great.

32:32.584 --> 32:33.801
Okay.

32:44.888 --> 32:46.936
[THOR GROWLING]

32:53.522 --> 32:55.445
In good time, old boy.

32:55.899 --> 32:57.276
In good time.

33:20.257 --> 33:21.429
Hey!

33:42.070 --> 33:43.822
[LAUGHING]

33:44.948 --> 33:46.291
It's not funny.

33:46.575 --> 33:48.418
He's turning into the Wolfman.

33:56.459 --> 33:58.645
I'm sorry, Brett, it's the full moon part.

33:58.795 --> 34:02.425
In movies, the guy only turns
into a werewolf during the full moon.

34:03.592 --> 34:05.610
Well, that's the way it works.

34:05.760 --> 34:08.572
When there's a full moon,
he turns into the werewolf.

34:08.722 --> 34:10.395
Everybody knows that.

34:11.766 --> 34:13.518
Why only the full moon?

34:13.810 --> 34:15.357
Why not any moon?

34:17.313 --> 34:20.041
Well, because that's the way
a werewolf works.

34:20.190 --> 34:22.569
You have to shoot him
with a silver bullet.

34:22.985 --> 34:26.202
I bet if you blew his head off
with a shotgun it would do quite nicely.

34:26.656 --> 34:29.375
Don't you know anything about werewolves?

34:30.118 --> 34:32.291
I know you turn into one
if you get bit by one.

34:32.786 --> 34:34.460
But the full moon part...

34:35.456 --> 34:37.016
Maybe there's different
kinds of werewolves,

34:37.167 --> 34:39.590
but it's been my experience
that any moon will do the trick.

34:40.295 --> 34:41.888
Werewolf-wise.

34:43.465 --> 34:45.388
Have you ever met a werewolf?

34:47.135 --> 34:49.558
I've been acquainted with
a few in my time.

34:50.513 --> 34:51.480
How about you?

34:51.681 --> 34:56.232
Come on. Everybody knows
there's no such thing as werewolves.

34:58.188 --> 34:59.405
Well...

34:59.773 --> 35:01.070
There you go.

35:02.317 --> 35:06.413
Brett, will you take the trash out
before breakfast, please?

35:08.073 --> 35:11.418
- Aw, Mom.
- Don't "Aw, Mom," me. Go.

35:25.215 --> 35:27.234
So, what all happened last night?

35:27.384 --> 35:28.681
I don't know really.

35:28.843 --> 35:31.530
Thor thought he heard something
in the woods, practically threw a fit.

35:31.680 --> 35:34.775
Woke up the whole house.
Lucky you were in the Airstream.

35:35.183 --> 35:36.910
Anyway, I finally let him out.

35:37.060 --> 35:39.438
He ran out into the woods
and he didn't come back.

35:39.688 --> 35:43.192
I tried calling him with that dog
whistle but he kept barking.

35:45.360 --> 35:46.703
So?

35:47.070 --> 35:48.538
What did he find?

35:49.239 --> 35:50.536
Nothing.

35:52.534 --> 35:54.628
What do you think it was all about?

35:55.412 --> 35:57.430
I don't know, really.
I'm not that worried.

35:57.580 --> 35:59.548
Thor barks at practically anything.

36:01.376 --> 36:02.878
I don't know, Janet.

36:03.878 --> 36:07.887
Big predators, they can travel a long
distance if their habitat runs dry.

36:08.091 --> 36:10.986
Just because there hasn't been
anything dangerous in this forest recently

36:11.136 --> 36:13.104
doesn't mean it's always gonna be safe.

36:13.888 --> 36:17.142
If I were you, I wouldn't let Brett
play out there for awhile until...

36:18.435 --> 36:19.732
Until what?

36:20.562 --> 36:22.914
There weren't supposed to be
any wolves up where I am.

36:23.064 --> 36:24.749
Look what happened to those people.

36:24.899 --> 36:26.572
I thought they said it was a grizzly bear.

36:26.943 --> 36:29.462
Janet, wolves, grizzly bears,
I mean it's the same difference!

36:29.612 --> 36:31.990
All I'm saying is you have
to be a little more cautious.

36:32.240 --> 36:35.119
Take the dog more seriously
and don't let him play out there.

36:35.952 --> 36:37.137
Don't you think you're overdoing it?

36:37.287 --> 36:39.460
I mean Thor isn't
exactly helpless, you know.

36:39.622 --> 36:41.340
Janet, how big is that dog?

36:41.791 --> 36:44.761
Get this, he's 105 pounds.

36:46.463 --> 36:49.512
Do you know how big a gray
wolf gets? Try 200 pounds!

36:52.302 --> 36:54.279
Give me a break, Ted.

36:54.429 --> 36:56.147
The dog starts barking at night

36:56.306 --> 36:59.435
and all of a sudden you've got
a 200-pound wolf at the door!

37:07.776 --> 37:09.619
Are you feeling okay?

37:20.622 --> 37:22.374
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

40:29.143 --> 40:31.237
[THOR GROWLING]

41:03.511 --> 41:04.763
Piss off.

41:13.855 --> 41:15.232
Hey, Janet.

41:16.232 --> 41:18.280
Could you take your dog
in the house, please!

41:19.318 --> 41:20.991
I'd like to go for a run.

41:29.037 --> 41:30.129
Come on, Thor.

41:32.206 --> 41:34.208
Come on, it's bedtime!

41:36.377 --> 41:38.220
Come on, Thor. Come on!

41:40.506 --> 41:41.849
Thor, come on!

41:44.469 --> 41:47.655
Thor, come on, it's bedtime! Come on in.

41:47.805 --> 41:49.648
Come on.

41:52.435 --> 41:54.688
Come on, come on. Good boy!

42:01.527 --> 42:02.995
Hey. Hey, hey, hey.

42:03.321 --> 42:04.288
Come here.

42:04.489 --> 42:06.036
What's up with you?

42:07.450 --> 42:09.452
Yeah, you be a good dog, huh?

42:09.702 --> 42:11.329
You be a good dog.

42:13.164 --> 42:15.642
Be a good dog.
Yeah, yeah, I love you, too.

42:15.792 --> 42:16.839
Good night.

42:29.222 --> 42:30.974
[THOR BARKING]

42:31.516 --> 42:33.484
- Hey.
- [BARKING CONTINUES]

42:36.979 --> 42:38.526
What's wrong, boy?

42:40.942 --> 42:42.364
You want to go out?

42:56.707 --> 42:58.630
[SNIFFING]

43:12.390 --> 43:14.017
[WHIMPERING]

43:22.942 --> 43:25.411
- [BARKING]
- [ROARING]

43:50.595 --> 43:52.597
[THOR WHINING]

43:53.055 --> 43:54.557
Thor?

43:55.183 --> 43:56.526
Hey, buddy.

43:59.896 --> 44:01.113
Come here.

44:02.315 --> 44:03.441
Come on.

44:06.319 --> 44:08.321
Hey, what happened to you?

44:10.156 --> 44:11.578
Oh, Thor.

44:13.159 --> 44:15.002
Who cut you?

44:15.494 --> 44:18.168
Oh, baby, who did this to you?

44:18.581 --> 44:21.050
Come on, let's go clean you up.

44:22.001 --> 44:23.924
Come on, it's okay.

44:24.378 --> 44:26.972
It's all right. Come on, sweetie.

44:27.798 --> 44:28.924
Come on.

44:30.551 --> 44:32.428
It's okay, come on.

44:41.729 --> 44:42.696
Hi.

44:42.855 --> 44:46.155
Yeah, this is Janet Harrison,
43 Oak Creek Lane.

44:47.235 --> 44:48.703
Hi, Sheriff.

45:30.653 --> 45:32.872
Ted? Are you in there?

45:33.614 --> 45:35.457
[GROWLING]

45:43.457 --> 45:45.130
Ted, you in here?

45:48.504 --> 45:49.471
Ted?

45:50.506 --> 45:51.883
[BOOK FALLS]

46:05.521 --> 46:06.647
Nice, Ted.

46:07.940 --> 46:09.487
[GASPING]

46:39.347 --> 46:42.442
December 28, 1995.

46:42.808 --> 46:44.105
Stateside.

46:44.518 --> 46:46.145
Saw a doctor here.

46:46.437 --> 46:47.984
Had blood test.

46:48.356 --> 46:50.609
Doctor couldn't identify strain.

46:50.941 --> 46:53.410
Some infection that isn't in the books.

46:53.861 --> 46:56.114
Had another blackout last night.

46:56.906 --> 46:58.374
Woke up in the woods.

47:02.870 --> 47:05.464
December 29, 1995.

47:05.956 --> 47:08.392
Blacked out again. Woke in the woods.

47:08.542 --> 47:09.602
Blood on me.

47:09.752 --> 47:10.969
Not mine.

47:24.683 --> 47:26.936
May 18, 1996.

47:28.229 --> 47:32.154
I have tried all medical
solutions to no effect.

47:32.400 --> 47:35.119
There is no known cure in medicine...

47:35.736 --> 47:37.079
but maybe...

47:37.530 --> 47:40.158
just maybe, there's hope for me.

47:40.658 --> 47:43.252
Janet and Brett came up to the lake today.

47:43.411 --> 47:46.210
To see her again did my heart good.

47:51.502 --> 47:53.971
She has invited me to stay with her.

47:54.380 --> 47:57.554
Perhaps if I spend time with her,
with my family...

47:58.467 --> 48:00.686
this disease will go into remission.

48:01.095 --> 48:03.848
Medicine will not stave off this disease.

48:04.348 --> 48:07.318
But perhaps love,
the restorative power of love,

48:07.560 --> 48:08.786
family love...

48:08.936 --> 48:10.511
will save me.

48:10.938 --> 48:12.656
It's my last chance.

48:57.985 --> 49:01.660
Nobody makes a fucking fool
out of me, lady.

49:06.494 --> 49:07.837
Here, doggie.

49:08.120 --> 49:09.597
Here, poochie, poochie.

49:09.747 --> 49:11.590
- [CLICKS TONGUE]
- [BLOWS KISSES]

49:12.875 --> 49:15.754
Come here, you frigging stupid dog.

49:16.670 --> 49:18.513
[GROWLING]

49:22.301 --> 49:23.974
Nice doggie.

49:25.971 --> 49:28.724
- [SCREAMING]
- [ROARING]

50:20.943 --> 50:22.786
Sheriff, where have you been?

50:27.866 --> 50:30.619
Is this the man who approached
your place last month?

50:33.747 --> 50:35.090
Yeah, it is.

50:36.333 --> 50:37.505
He's dead.

50:39.461 --> 50:41.429
His name is Jerry Mills.

50:42.590 --> 50:45.801
We found him on the road, a couple
hundred yards from your house.

50:47.094 --> 50:49.597
He bore the marks of an animal attack.

50:50.097 --> 50:53.772
He's been torn open
by a big animal like a wolf or...

50:54.602 --> 50:56.354
Or a dog, is that it?

50:56.729 --> 50:57.946
Yes, ma'am.

50:58.355 --> 51:02.697
I do recall you told me the last time
Thor almost took a bite out of Mills.

51:03.736 --> 51:07.240
Well, maybe last night when Mills
came back, Thor went at him again.

51:07.698 --> 51:09.700
[POLICE RADIO CHATTER IN BACKGROUND]

51:11.118 --> 51:13.166
Thor got in a fight last night...

51:14.413 --> 51:15.960
with something or...

51:17.750 --> 51:19.172
someone.

51:20.628 --> 51:22.521
He's got cuts all over him.

51:22.671 --> 51:23.797
I see.

51:30.095 --> 51:33.975
You know about these slayings
up in the Timberline area...

51:36.727 --> 51:38.695
those hikers that were killed?

51:39.146 --> 51:40.489
Yes, Janet.

51:41.231 --> 51:43.450
That wouldn't be the same
animal that killed Mills.

51:43.651 --> 51:46.746
It would've had to travel 200 miles
from Timberline to get here.

51:46.945 --> 51:48.538
That's not what I mean.

51:50.157 --> 51:51.704
My question is...

51:52.660 --> 51:54.708
is it possible that...

51:55.913 --> 51:58.086
they were committed by a human being?

52:01.126 --> 52:02.753
No chance at all, Janet.

52:04.004 --> 52:05.972
They were done by a big animal.

52:06.590 --> 52:10.720
No man could tear a person apart the way
the beast that butchered those people did.

52:11.595 --> 52:13.563
The same with Mills last night.

52:14.264 --> 52:16.437
Wolves are the probable culprits.

52:16.600 --> 52:19.149
Very, very big wolves, but not a man.

52:19.520 --> 52:21.238
Not humanly possible.

52:22.106 --> 52:23.449
Why did you ask?

52:26.360 --> 52:27.782
I don't know.

52:31.782 --> 52:34.911
I reckon that's all for now, Janet.
I'll be in touch.

52:35.994 --> 52:37.166
Thanks.

52:39.498 --> 52:40.670
Just one thing.

52:43.043 --> 52:44.636
I know you love Thor.

52:45.754 --> 52:48.803
And if he did tear up Mills,
he was doing so to protect you.

52:50.175 --> 52:53.070
But once a dog becomes a biter,
gets a taste for human blood,

52:53.220 --> 52:54.655
he becomes dangerous.

52:54.805 --> 52:57.775
I suggest you consider
shopping for another hound.

53:20.873 --> 53:22.591
Good morning, there, big guy.

53:24.418 --> 53:26.341
How are you doing this morning?

53:27.379 --> 53:29.882
Want to go outside, Thor, huh?

53:30.090 --> 53:31.967
Want to go outside? Come on.

53:40.434 --> 53:42.311
Right to the Airstream.

54:31.401 --> 54:33.620
Where were you last night, Ted?

54:37.282 --> 54:38.659
I went for a run.

54:39.117 --> 54:40.414
All night?

54:42.329 --> 54:43.876
You didn't see anything?

54:44.498 --> 54:45.875
Hear anything?

54:48.836 --> 54:50.804
- [BARKING]
- [SCREAMING]

54:51.129 --> 54:52.426
Get him off me!

54:52.673 --> 54:53.799
No! Don't!

54:55.843 --> 54:57.236
Get in the trailer!

54:57.386 --> 54:59.229
No, Thor! Stop it!

54:59.471 --> 55:00.393
Get him off!

55:01.473 --> 55:02.895
Thor, get off!

55:05.477 --> 55:06.649
Thor, no!

55:06.937 --> 55:09.235
Get in the house! I can't hold him back!

55:11.942 --> 55:14.195
Thor! Come on!

55:14.611 --> 55:16.329
Come on! Come on! Come on!

55:16.989 --> 55:19.208
[BARKING CONTINUES]

55:19.491 --> 55:22.290
Thor, come on! Bad dog! Bad dog!

55:23.161 --> 55:25.334
Stop it, Thor! Come on! Calm down!

55:27.708 --> 55:28.925
Get in there!

55:31.295 --> 55:33.172
[THOR WHIMPERING]

56:08.874 --> 56:10.046
Come here, Thor.

56:11.043 --> 56:13.592
Come on, sweetie. Come on.

56:14.379 --> 56:16.940
Come on. It's okay. It's okay. I'm sorry.

56:17.090 --> 56:19.267
Come on. Come on.

56:19.593 --> 56:21.345
I'm sorry, babe.

56:21.970 --> 56:24.689
- Go on, it's okay.
- Hold his head.

56:25.057 --> 56:26.867
It's okay, Thor. Go on.

56:27.017 --> 56:28.118
Okay. Good boy.

56:28.268 --> 56:29.620
I got him.

56:29.770 --> 56:31.288
[THOR BARKING]

56:31.438 --> 56:33.207
Thor! Come back!

56:33.357 --> 56:35.417
- Thor!
- Brett, come here. Come on, sweety.

56:35.567 --> 56:38.867
They have to take him.
There's nothing we can do about it.

56:39.571 --> 56:40.743
Don't go!

56:41.531 --> 56:42.874
They'll kill him!

56:44.701 --> 56:47.420
They have to take him, Brett.
He's dangerous!

56:47.579 --> 56:50.503
No, it's not true, Mom! It's not true!

56:50.958 --> 56:52.460
Thor!

56:53.377 --> 56:54.879
Thor!

56:59.466 --> 57:00.934
Let go!

57:01.635 --> 57:03.512
Mom, they're going to kill him!

57:04.179 --> 57:06.022
He's going to die!

57:06.974 --> 57:08.066
Let go!

57:10.769 --> 57:13.898
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

57:16.942 --> 57:18.239
It's okay.

57:20.737 --> 57:22.489
[THOR BARKING]

57:26.868 --> 57:28.336
It's okay.

57:30.372 --> 57:32.215
Come on! Come on!

57:35.836 --> 57:37.179
I know.

57:40.799 --> 57:42.221
It's okay.

59:02.547 --> 59:04.174
It's probably genetic.

59:04.591 --> 59:07.720
It happens with Shepherds.
It's the way they breed them.

59:11.598 --> 59:13.350
Thor's pedigreed.

59:14.101 --> 59:16.195
It doesn't happen to pedigrees.

59:25.112 --> 59:27.114
You're gonna have to see a
doctor for that.

59:27.989 --> 59:30.538
No, I won't. It's just a flesh wound.

59:31.159 --> 59:34.538
No veins or tendons were cut.
Nothing I can't take care of.

59:38.041 --> 59:39.918
You're gonna need a tetanus shot.

59:42.295 --> 59:44.514
I can give myself a tetanus shot, Janet.

59:50.178 --> 59:51.851
Excuse me a second.

01:00:16.037 --> 01:00:18.165
I'm sorry about your dog, son.

01:00:25.839 --> 01:00:27.136
Come here.

01:00:32.220 --> 01:00:33.847
Come here!

01:00:51.239 --> 01:00:53.617
There'll be other animals in your life.

01:00:59.998 --> 01:01:02.922
Brett. It's time for bed.

01:01:11.593 --> 01:01:12.970
I'll be right up.

01:01:31.488 --> 01:01:33.240
I guess I'll turn in, too.

01:01:40.288 --> 01:01:41.380
Ted.

01:01:43.124 --> 01:01:44.592
Yes, Janet?

01:01:49.214 --> 01:01:51.091
If I ask you a question...

01:01:53.260 --> 01:01:54.978
will you tell me the truth?

01:01:55.512 --> 01:01:56.855
Of course.

01:01:59.766 --> 01:02:01.109
Where's Marjorie?

01:02:02.269 --> 01:02:03.521
Seattle.

01:04:47.934 --> 01:04:50.232
[DOGS BARKING]

01:05:11.040 --> 01:05:12.434
Come on!

01:05:12.584 --> 01:05:14.144
[DOGS BARKING]

01:05:14.294 --> 01:05:15.546
Oh, shit!

01:05:26.973 --> 01:05:28.475
Hey, Thor!

01:05:46.618 --> 01:05:47.710
Company?

01:05:48.495 --> 01:05:50.497
Just what I came here to get away from.

01:05:53.666 --> 01:05:54.963
Sis?

01:05:55.502 --> 01:05:56.970
Janet?

01:05:57.504 --> 01:06:00.383
- Is it you?
- Yeah, Ted.

01:06:01.007 --> 01:06:03.226
What the hell's going on?

01:06:06.262 --> 01:06:08.515
Playing Nancy Drew, are we, sis?

01:06:10.517 --> 01:06:13.203
You caught me at a rather awkward moment.

01:06:13.353 --> 01:06:14.900
I was just about to...

01:06:15.563 --> 01:06:17.281
restrain myself.

01:06:17.524 --> 01:06:21.044
But now that you're already here,
that might be somewhat pointless.

01:06:21.194 --> 01:06:23.947
You're going to come clean
with me right now!

01:06:25.031 --> 01:06:27.580
[GROANING]

01:06:34.832 --> 01:06:36.550
Family love, Janet.

01:06:39.712 --> 01:06:42.807
I thought it could save me,
but I was wrong.

01:06:45.718 --> 01:06:47.812
But, hey, we all make mistakes!

01:06:49.180 --> 01:06:51.603
You sent the dog to the pound, Janet.

01:06:53.268 --> 01:06:54.736
I warned you.

01:06:55.436 --> 01:06:58.315
I told you I shouldn't be here,
but you wouldn't let me go.

01:06:59.816 --> 01:07:01.910
You wanted to play big sister.

01:07:02.443 --> 01:07:04.161
You had to be right.

01:07:04.612 --> 01:07:08.037
You always have to be right, Janet,
but this time you're wrong!

01:07:10.076 --> 01:07:12.670
You should have listened
to the dog, Janet.

01:07:13.413 --> 01:07:15.586
He was trying to protect you.

01:07:19.294 --> 01:07:22.013
- [BONES CRUNCHING]
- [GROANING]

01:07:31.973 --> 01:07:33.225
Ted?

01:07:38.938 --> 01:07:42.112
Handcuffs. I was going to
use these on myself.

01:07:43.985 --> 01:07:46.829
- Can you believe that?
- What's happening?

01:07:47.864 --> 01:07:52.953
They, they were supposed to keep
people from finding out about my...

01:07:53.620 --> 01:07:55.338
private affair.

01:07:55.955 --> 01:07:57.457
My mistress.

01:07:57.999 --> 01:07:59.296
Oh, my God.

01:07:59.792 --> 01:08:01.044
But, you...

01:08:01.461 --> 01:08:03.429
You already know, don't you, sis?

01:08:04.005 --> 01:08:06.099
[SCREAMING]

01:08:09.636 --> 01:08:11.934
Yes, you know...

01:08:13.681 --> 01:08:18.187
the handcuffs won't keep my little
secret a secret any longer.

01:08:19.520 --> 01:08:21.113
Come back!

01:08:22.357 --> 01:08:24.779
You stupid bitch!

01:08:31.491 --> 01:08:33.885
Thor! I'm gonna get you out!

01:08:34.035 --> 01:08:35.627
Here, come on!

01:08:40.667 --> 01:08:42.840
[ROARING]

01:08:45.505 --> 01:08:46.631
Come here, Thor!

01:08:47.590 --> 01:08:50.890
All right, Thor, come on! Quick!
You're free! Let's go!

01:08:51.803 --> 01:08:53.645
[PANICKED GASPING]

01:08:54.721 --> 01:08:56.599
[THOR BARKING]

01:09:05.733 --> 01:09:07.406
Thor, we've gotta get outta here!

01:09:14.408 --> 01:09:16.207
Oh, yes!

01:09:53.823 --> 01:09:56.968
[CAR HORN BLARING]

01:09:57.118 --> 01:09:58.928
